title: Grateful Dead Live at Hollywood Palladium on 1972-09-09
lineage: AUD > MR > Cassette (unknown gen) > Nakamichi DR3 > Audacity > CD Wave > FLAC16
description:
Set 1: Promised Land, Sugaree, Me And My Uncle, Bird Song, Black-Throated Wind, Tennessee Jed, Mexicali Blues, Deal, Playin' In The Band, Loser, Johnny B. Goode

Set 2: China Cat Sunflower > I Know You Rider, Friend Of The Devil, Jack Straw, He's Gone, Truckin' > Drums > The Other One > Space > The Other One, El Paso, Casey Jones, Sugar Magnolia

reviews.review_text: New Stuff! Pitched down a whole step, i believe.  Great sounding audience, though, thank you friends....

Memories... This was one of the first GD shows I ever got on tape. As such it had a HUGE influence on me, and is still one of my favorite Dead tapes. Tripped out to this baby many times!
This is definitely from the same source as my old tapes - amazing recording for '72, although it does run slow as noted below (hence 4 stars). Nothing that Cool Edit can't fix :)
slooooow... not sure which sounds worse, this aud or the sbd...

pitch problems i recently downloaded and speed corrected this show. i will upload the corrected file to the archive just as soon as i figure out how to do so.if you are a fan of '72, and who isn't, you will really enjoy this show. so if you are planning on partaking of this particular download, hold off until i get it uploaded unless you plan to speed it up for yourself
Good Aud If you're looking for an aud from 72 it probably doesn't get much better than this. Listening to Bird right now and its ripping crispy style. I'm downloading.
